-- Iberdrola Studies Bid for U.K. Nuclear Sites, Expansion Reports
-- B y   T o d d   W h i t e
-- 2012-05-07T06:15:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/iberdrola-studies-bid-for-u-k-nuclear-sites-expansion-reports.html
Iberdrola SA (IBE)  is one of several
companies studying whether to bid for a U.K. company that has
two sites suitable for building nuclear reactors, Expansion
reported, citing unidentified people in the industry.  The Spanish power company is analyzing Horizon Nuclear
Power, a venture of  RWE AG (RWE)  and EON AG, as a possible acquisition
target by its NuGen venture with  GDF Suez (GSZ) , the Spanish newspaper
said. NuGen would have to pay about 300 million pounds ($485
million) for Horizon, according to analysts, the report said.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
